{"id": "EUVD-2025-19830", "enisaUuid": "cfdba1f1-7f32-3243-bdf8-7cd2bb11d004", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nACPI: CPPC: Fix NULL pointer dereference when nosmp is used\n\nWith nosmp in cmdline, other CPUs are not brought up, leaving\ntheir cpc_desc_ptr NULL. CPU0's iteration via for_each_possible_cpu()\ndereferences these NULL pointers, causing panic.\n\nPanic backtrace:\n\n[    0.401123] Unable to handle kernel NULL pointer dereference at virtual address 00000000000000b8\n...\n[    0.403255] [<ffffffff809a5818>] cppc_allow_fast_switch+0x6a/0xd4\n...\nKernel panic - not syncing: Attempted to kill init!\n\n[ rjw: New subject ]", "datePublished": "2025-07-03T09:30:33", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-17T18:31:31", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/356d09c7f5bf525086002a34f8bae40b134d1611", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/c6dad167aade4bf0bef9130f2f149f4249fc4ad0", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/32a48db4cf28ea087214c261da8476db218d08bd", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/1a677d0ceb4a5d62117b711a8b2e0aee80d33015", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/15eece6c5b05e5f9db0711978c3e3b7f1a2cfe12", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-38113", "https://lists.debian.org/debian-lts-announce/2025/10/msg00008.html"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-38113"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.03, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "0ad23ddf-d577-3981-b1c2-d10bddb5a07e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.1.142"}, {"id": "1f5c8cc8-2bc5-3897-9dd6-12e96b0938c2", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.16"}, {"id": "216b40a1-0d33-3257-8bb9-01a4ff5950ab", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.6.94"}, {"id": "682b837a-51cf-36cf-9caf-0808ea9bfe20", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "3cc30dd00a580ca0c9c0b01639841cfd72d10129 <15eece6c5b05e5f9db0711978c3e3b7f1a2cfe12"}, {"id": "69b680df-7b61-302d-a101-fa20d95bc16b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "produc